i need you to create complete custom model architecture for GNN using GAT with the architecture is control by the PPO RL agent using actor and critic network.

Create custom GNN(GAT) Model Architecture: Create distinct pathways for component nodes and net nodes within your model, where only component nodes’ pathways have trainable parameters, and net nodes’ pathways are either parameter-free or have all parameters frozen. You could achieve this by selectively applying the GNN operations only to the component nodes and concatenating the output with the untouched features of the net nodes for any subsequent operations or decisions.

The custom model must be properly synchronized with the RL PPO agent with actor and critic network.

Selective Parameter Update: During the training loop, we need adjust the gradient updates to exclude any updates that would affect the “frozen” features.

In PyTorch, parameters (or parts of them) can be frozen by setting requires_grad to False.

To achieve the goal of ensuring that only specific node features (the ones associated with the component nodes) are updated during the training process while other node features (the ones associated with the net nodes) remain unchanged, we need to take a somewhat different approach than merely adjusting input features. Since we are using a Deep Learning framework (PyTorch), direct control over which parts of the input get updated during backpropagation isn’t straightforward because input features themselves do not have gradients that get updated. Instead, model parameters (weights) get updated.

My requirement is,
Graph contains 20 nodes among total 20 nodes, 11 nodes are component nodes (which are need to be tune with in the bounds by optimization technique) other 9 nodes are net nodes(these net nodes and its respective features need not to be tune/change during the training process all the features need to be fixed). each nodes contains the its features in 'node_features_tensor'.
node_features_tensor = state (preprocessed tensor structure of  Normalized scalar values and one hot representation for string data) with indices structure as [0:24] for each node,

we can differentiate the component node and the net node at the index [0] if the value is '0' then it is component node if the value is '1' then it is net node(ensure the features of net nodes are need to be unchange)

from these selected 11 component nodes, each component nodes has the index values of [0:24] features for each, but we need to concentrate on tuning the particular index values for each respective node.
we need to identify and select the required 11 nodes among the selected component nodes in the 'node_features_tensor',
